Isabella Carapella / HuffPost and Erica Aitken Photography Some of the more than 20 women who have accused President Donald Trump of sexual misconduct and harassment; Alva Johnson in center.
Other women who have publicly accused Trump of sexual misconduct and misbehavior are disappointed he has faced no repercussions, several told HuffPost.
“It seems right now we’re going backward,” Johnson told Teen Vogue in an interview published this month.
Women who’ve accused Trump of sexual misconduct would also like to see him face consequences — but they aren’t optimistic.
The women HuffPost spoke with said they would still encourage women to come forward with their experiences.